"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-11-paris-2024-olympic-highlights-brightest-stars-city-lights-21403457\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paris2024 produced a multitude of memories - from Keely Hodgkinson's dominant 800metres triumph, to Alex Yee's thrilling triathlon victory.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 50, \"end\": 66, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From French passion and success, to Noah Lyles being crowned the fastest man in the world.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 146, \"end\": 152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.6400710112356842, \"rank\": 0.3954941150866062, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 177, \"end\": 187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition has also produced its fair share of emotion asAndy Murraybid farewell to tennis, while a binned note stirred up emotions for gold-medal winning rower Lola Anderson.\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 398, \"end\": 402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lola_Cars\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.231425890201631e-14, \"text\": \"Lola\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lola_Cars\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lola_Cars\"}, {\"begin\": 403, \"end\": 411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Anderson\", \"score\": 0.9996790676510792, \"rank\": 0.0003210353797043098, \"text\": \"Anderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Anderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Anderson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After another unforgettableOlympic Games, we pick out our highlights:  Poster boyAntoine Dupontled France to their first gold in the rugby sevens.\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 513, \"end\": 519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9973841785636214, \"rank\": 0.0026226268994508136, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He skipped the Six Nations to focus on the Olympics and his gamble paid off with a match-winning display in the final in front of the sort of passionate crowd which would become synonymous with the games.\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Teddy Riner - who kicked things off by lighting the Olympic cauldron - and Leon Marchand were two other big stars for the inspired hosts.\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}, {\"begin\": 847, \"end\": 855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.033802150661629e-15, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles capped off her Olympic return in style with three golds and a silver medal.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a redemptive return for the American gymnast, who withdrew in Tokyo due to the 'twisties' and had A-list celebrities flocking to Paris to see her perform.\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1031, \"end\": 1039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999686518902323, \"rank\": 0.0002574424652456373, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1065, \"end\": 1070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.583610931004486, \"rank\": 0.7134703050854392, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1132, \"end\": 1137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7238235616581666e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy Murray bid goodbye to tennis with defeat alongside Dan Evans in the quarter-finals of the men's doubles.\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1159, \"end\": 1170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.51235386708368e-47, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\", \"score\": 0.7586767867691373, \"rank\": 0.3180843508384847, \"text\": \"Dan Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the duo entertained crowds with two dramatic victories at Roland Garros, saving multiple match points along the way.\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am glad I got to go out here at the Olympics and finish on my terms,' said Murray.\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1470, \"end\": 1476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.132960893601327e-24, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I feel lucky I got to play some great matches and create amazing memories.'\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1554, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 was a bit of a transition Games for Team GB - Laura Kenny gone, Murray going and boxing and taekwondo struggling to deliver medals.\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1698, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\"}, {\"begin\": 1631, \"end\": 1637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.132960893601327e-24, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we did see triathlete Alex Yee and cyclist Tom Pidcock confirm their class with gold medals at consecutive Olympics, both won with daring late comebacks fit to inspire the next generation and ensure their places as British Olympic legends.\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1726, \"end\": 1734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 1919, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9983981458752361, \"rank\": 0.001335094266248313, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Noah Lyles claimed gold after a photo finish in the men's 100m final.\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 2014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1945, \"end\": 1955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old American lived up to his considerable hype by pipping Jamaica's Kishane Thompson to victory by just five thousandths of a second, in the closest and fastest edition of the blue-riband event.\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2221, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2031, \"end\": 2039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999686518902323, \"rank\": 0.0002574424652456373, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2085, \"end\": 2092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9278379420707902, \"rank\": 0.07769250052495381, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 2103, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9525988980465397, \"rank\": 0.049759769856679854, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid a much-improved showing from Team GB's rowers one emotional story stood out.\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lola Anderson took gold in the quadruple sculls, inspired by her late father who had reminded her of a childhood diary entry in which she dreamed of one day emulating London 2012 star Helen Glover - also in the team in Paris and winning silver.\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2306, \"end\": 2310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lola_Cars\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.231425890201631e-14, \"text\": \"Lola\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lola_Cars\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lola_Cars\"}, {\"begin\": 2311, \"end\": 2319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Anderson\", \"score\": 0.9996790676510792, \"rank\": 0.0003210353797043098, \"text\": \"Anderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Anderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Anderson\"}, {\"begin\": 2473, \"end\": 2484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.347198517519853e-16, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2490, \"end\": 2502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}, {\"begin\": 2525, \"end\": 2530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7238235616581666e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Agonising silver medals for Josh Kerr and Matt Hudson-Smith were no shame given the level of competition on the track but there was no upsetting Keely Hodgkinson (left, bottom), who dominated the women's 800m.\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2580, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.9997898927971532, \"rank\": 7.735529942014652e-05, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}, {\"begin\": 2697, \"end\": 2713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB bagged their 1,000th medal at summer and winter Games, in Paris - the honour going to the men's cycling team pursuit squad.\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2763, \"end\": 2770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0457217864922185e-16, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2829, \"end\": 2834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7238235616581666e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The British riders narrowly missed out on gold in the final against Australia and their hopes were effectively over when Hayter slipped from his saddle on the final lap.\", \"from\": 2896, \"to\": 3065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2900, \"end\": 2907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9983981458752361, \"rank\": 0.001335094266248313, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2964, \"end\": 2973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9991284058758573, \"rank\": 0.0008677957008424827, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3017, \"end\": 3023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanley_William_Hayter\", \"score\": 0.9999984897624508, \"rank\": 1.5102397984389896e-06, \"text\": \"Hayter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanley_William_Hayter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanley_William_Hayter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking afterwards, Bigham said: 'It's nice to win a medal, it's nice to win a silver medal, it's nice for it to be the thousandth GB medal.\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3199, \"end\": 3201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999938337049603, \"rank\": 6.166330427340177e-06, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's nice to ride in an Olympic gold medal final with these guys.'\", \"from\": 3209, \"to\": 3275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.\", \"from\": 3327, \"to\": 3397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Team GB flag bearer among athletes who nearly trip over during Paris Olympics closing ceremony  ArrowMORE:Prince William and Kate Middleton send message to Team GB with Snoop Dogg after Olympics ends  ArrowMORE:Olympics star responds to fan backlash after not sharing gold medal with rival  Get your favourite puzzles when they are ready to play on the website sent directly to you every day and track your daily streak!\", \"from\": 3399, \"to\": 3829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3515, \"end\": 3529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_IV\", \"score\": 0.9977431657845657, \"rank\": 0.0015901131178415056, \"text\": \"Prince William\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_IV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_IV\"}, {\"begin\": 3534, \"end\": 3548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine,_Duchess_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.999999977424522